      <lg xml:id="TolE0239">
<l>patakkumuṉ variṉē tūṇik kiḷavi</l>
<l>mutaṟkiḷan teṭutta vēṟṟumai yiyaṟṟē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">tūṇi</foreign> ' a measure of 4 marcals ' precedes</l>
<l>the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">patakku</foreign> ' a measure of 2 marcals ',</l>
<l>it is the same as the case-relation mentioned before.<note place="foot">i.e., <foreign xml:lang="ta">p</foreign> is inserted, <foreign xml:lang="ta">tūṇippatakku.</foreign> We would expect <foreign xml:lang="ta">*tūṇiyē patakku</foreign> accord. to 165.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
